07/01/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivica Racan said in a TV interview Sunday (5 January) that the period of national "belt-tightening" has ended and that the standard of living would continue to improve. He predicted a slight growth in wages and confirmed plans to submit an official application for EU membership in February, saying the time is right. (HINA, HRT - 06/01/03; HRT - 05/01/03)
